HEADWORD: Consultive
<hw>Con*sult"ive</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧n*s⟦ucr⟧lt"⟦icr⟧v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Determined by, or pertaining to, consultation; deliberate;
consultative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that remains in the grace of God sins not by any deliberative,
<qex>consultive</qex>, knowing act.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Consumable</ent>⟦br⟧
